  <li><p> Consider the matrix
  <me>
  A = \left[\begin{array}{rrr}
  3 \amp 2 \amp 0 \\
  -1 \amp 0 \amp -2 \\
  2 \amp 1 \amp 1
  \end{array}\right]
  </me>
  whose columns we denote by <m>\vvec_1</m>, <m>\vvec_2</m>, and
  <m>\vvec_3</m>.
  Are the vectors <m>\vvec_1</m>, <m>\vvec_2</m>, and
  <m>\vvec_3</m> linearly dependent or independent?
  <sage>
    <input>
